1 Flow cytometry data analysis

We perform analysis of flow cytometry data from the flowRepository accession FR_FCM_Z3WR. Data was analyzed with R version 4.3.1 (2023-06-16). Most analysis steps were performed using the following packages: flowCore (v2.12.2), CATALYST (v1.24.0).

# load libraries
library(flowCore)
library(CATALYST)
library(cowplot)

1.1 A clean flowSet output by flow AI is imported.

# 1) load the flowSet object from exercise 3
load("../course_datasets/FR_FCM_Z3WR/fcs_clean.RData")

# 2) Downsample to 2'000 cells 

# source downsampling function
source("../course_datasets/function_for_downsampling_flowSets.R")

# downsample
set.seed(1234)
fcs_small <- Downsampling_flowSet(fcs_clean,samplesize = 2000)

# 3) Create a sce object from the downsampled flowSet
# We need the panel data frame
panel <- read.csv("../course_datasets/FR_FCM_Z3WR/panel_with_marker_classes.csv")

# We also need a metadata dataframe
md <- pData(fcs_small)

# create sce
sce <- prepData(fcs_small, 
                md = md,
                md_cols = list(file="name", id = "name", factors = "time_point"),
                panel = panel,
                panel_cols = list(channel = "channels", antigen = "antigen", class = "marker_class"),
                transform = FALSE,
                FACS=TRUE,
                features = panel$channels[panel$marker_class!="none"])

# change the assay name to "exprs" 
assayNames(sce) <- "exprs"

1.2 The UMAP is computed using default parameters

Parameters = n_neighbors=15 and min_dist = 0.01.

# 4) UMAP with default parameters (n_neighbors=15 and min_dist = 0.01)
set.seed(1601)
sce <- runDR(sce, 
             assay = "exprs", 
             dr = "UMAP", 
             features = "type", 
             cells = NULL)

1.3 UMAP of down-sampled cells

1.3.1 CD3 expression

# plot
plotDR(sce,
       dr =  "UMAP",
       assay = "exprs", 
       color_by="CD3", 
       facet_by = "time_point" )

1.4 UMAP of down-sampled cells

1.4.1 CD8 and CD4 expression

Using plot_grid()

# plot CD4
p1<-plotDR(sce,
       dr =  "UMAP",
       assay = "exprs", 
       color_by="CD4")

# plot CD4
p2<-plotDR(sce,
       dr =  "UMAP",
       assay = "exprs", 
       color_by="CD8")

plot_grid(p1, p2, nrow = 2)

1.5 UMAP of down-sampled cells

CD19 and CD56 expression

Providing a vector with several antigens to the plotDR() function, this also creates a grid.

# provide 2 genes
plotDR(sce,
       dr =  "UMAP",
       assay = "exprs", 
       color_by=c("CD19", "CD56"))
